  "text": "Most practical applications require either onedimensional (1D), or multi-dimensional DFFTs with up to a few thousand data values in each dimension. In this paper, we focus on the relatively exotic domain of 1D DFTs of data sets with a few billion data values (i.e., N 10 9 ). This domain of DFTs has application in astronomy (e.g., [CITATION_1] ), however, because of its rare occurrence in other fields, existing tools for performing such DFTs are not tuned for multi-core CPUs and perform sub-optimally.",
